Sentencas: La2Ni0.9Fe0.1O4+delta (LNF) with a K2NiF4-type structure is synthesized with a citrate complexing method and used as an anode material of a solid oxide fuel cell.
Titulo: Improve electrical conductivity of reduced La2Ni0.9Fe0.1O4+δ as the anode of a solid oxide fuel cell by carbon deposition

Sentencas: It is reduced to La2O3 and Ni-Fe alloy phases in H-2 atmosphere.
Titulo: Improve electrical conductivity of reduced La2Ni0.9Fe0.1O4+δ as the anode of a solid oxide fuel cell by carbon deposition

Sentencas: The electrical conductivity of the anode material is enhanced by carbon deposition with CH4 and methanol as the carbon sources, respectively.
Titulo: Improve electrical conductivity of reduced La2Ni0.9Fe0.1O4+δ as the anode of a solid oxide fuel cell by carbon deposition

Sentencas: The deposited carbon is characterized with a scanning electron microscope, a transmission electron microscope, thermogravimetric analysis and a Raman spectrometer.
Titulo: Improve electrical conductivity of reduced La2Ni0.9Fe0.1O4+δ as the anode of a solid oxide fuel cell by carbon deposition

Sentencas: The carbon deposited from methanol has a higher degree of graphitization than that from CH4, bringing about a higher electrical conductivity.
Titulo: Improve electrical conductivity of reduced La2Ni0.9Fe0.1O4+δ as the anode of a solid oxide fuel cell by carbon deposition

Sentencas: The conductivity of the reduced LNF at 800 degrees C increases from 0.23 S cm(-1) to 2.47 S cm(-1) after the carbon deposition in methanol.
Titulo: Improve electrical conductivity of reduced La2Ni0.9Fe0.1O4+δ as the anode of a solid oxide fuel cell by carbon deposition

Sentencas: The increase of the anode conductivity results in an improvement of the fuel cell performance.
Titulo: Improve electrical conductivity of reduced La2Ni0.9Fe0.1O4+δ as the anode of a solid oxide fuel cell by carbon deposition

Sentencas: A maximum power density of 166 mW cm(-2) is obtained at 800 degrees C from a single cell with La0.8Sr0.2Ga0.83Mg0.17O3-delta as the electrolyte and Ba0.5Sr0.5CO0.8Fe0.2O3-delta as the cathode.
Titulo: Improve electrical conductivity of reduced La2Ni0.9Fe0.1O4+δ as the anode of a solid oxide fuel cell by carbon deposition
